VALUES ('7124650c-9344-4e64-8e74-63f111ae9bf5', 'Which choice completes the text with the most logical transition?', 'When researchers introduced wolves back into a national park, they expected the predators to affect only the deer population. The wolves did reduce deer numbers, but the changes rippled much further than anyone predicted. ______ riverbanks once stripped bare by grazing deer grew lush with returning vegetation, altering the very course of the streams.', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"By contrast,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: the riverbank change is an example of the wider rippling, not a contrast."},{"id":"B","text":"Nevertheless,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: the lush growth supports the claim of far-reaching effects rather than opposing it."},{"id":"C","text":"For example,","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: the riverbank transformation is a concrete instance of the wider ripple just mentioned."},{"id":"D","text":"Therefore,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: the sentence illustrates the claim rather than drawing a conclusion from it."}]'::jsonb, 'C', 'Step 1 — Identify the relationship
The text says the changes {{yellow:rippled much further than anyone predicted}}.
Step 2 — Match the transition
The final sentence gives a specific instance of those far-reaching effects, so an example transition fits.
Distractor analysis:
- A: ''By contrast'' implies opposition, but the riverbank case supports the claim.
- B: ''Nevertheless'' marks concession the text does not need.
- D: ''Therefore'' would draw a conclusion, but the sentence supplies an illustration.', 'The last sentence gives one concrete case of the ''further ripples.''', 'Expression of Ideas', 'Transitions', 'reading_writing', 'expression', 'TRA', NULL, 'medium', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"generator":"scholaris_ai_v1","model":"gemma-4-26b-a4b-it","original":true,"explanation_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now())
